      "writtenOn": "2020-08-08T00:58:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How is this kAOnly? Isn\u0027t everything outside b.innerBounds affected by b if it\u0027s a difference op?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 66,
        "startChar": 37,
        "endLine": 66,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "4a05b18d81a033fd995d1494647ca2acc250308c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e57dd7a1_392284c1",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrClipStack.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 66,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-10T15:35:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since \"B\" is a difference op, everything inside b\u0027s inner bounds (or its contains function) has 0 coverage. Between its inner and outer bounds has undetermined coverage between 0 and 1. Everything outside of b\u0027s outer bounds has full coverage.\n\nIf the intersection element \"A\" is completely outside of \"B\"\u0027s outer bounds, then \"A\" is only intersecting the full coverage portion of B so it\u0027s no different than just being kAOnly.",
      "parentUuid": "574adf6d_1e679edb",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 66,
        "startChar": 37,
        "endLine": 66,
        "endChar": 43
      },
      "revId": "4a05b18d81a033fd995d1494647ca2acc250308c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d41e2cb3_81cf69cf",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrClipStack.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 94,
      "author": {
        "id": 5633
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-08T00:58:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "How can a.contains(b) be true? Is there an implicit render target clip on b? Otherwise it is infinitely large, correct?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 94,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "4a05b18d81a033fd995d1494647ca2acc250308c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f377f47d_2b69bb8d",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrClipStack.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 8
      },
      "lineNbr": 94,
      "author": {
        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-10T15:35:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "contains() is purely geometric, and elements\u0027 shapes are never inverse filled. From that standpoint, a diff \"A\" can still contain a diff \"B\" since it\u0027s just testing if the cut-out shape of B is contained in the cut-out shape of A. When that happens, the infinitely large covered region outside of B will be clipped to A\u0027s shape still, so kAOnly is the a valid simplification.",
      "parentUuid": "d41e2cb3_81cf69cf",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 94,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "4a05b18d81a033fd995d1494647ca2acc250308c",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
